      <bioghist id="aspace_3cbbfafc071874f2574d6e44be3a4207">
         <head>Historical Note</head>
         <p>The Women in Campus Ministry organization was founded in 1974 and changed its name to Campus Ministry Women in 1975. Campus Ministry Women was a national organization of Catholic, Protestant, and Jewish women who were involved in ministry in higher education. It provided a communications network, sponsored conferences and educational experiences, and served as a support and advocacy organization. The organization disbanded in 1996.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_486c90ad5cc5c70dfd2fbcab4dd907b9">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>This collection is open for research.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_dcb8a75f369311b351e3f6c20050adc4">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>Legal documents, minutes, financial records, programmatic material, correspondence, and newsletters document the formation and work of Campus Ministry Women.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_a7dbe78a7fd1cd562240e473a43727c7">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The collection is arranged in three series:</p>
         <p>I. Administrative Records</p>
         <p>II. Correspondence</p>
         <p>III. Newsletters</p>  
      </arrangement>
